Open your project in VS Code and open the Integrated Terminal.
Navigate to View > Terminal or use the shortcut Ctrl+ (backtick).
Initialize a Git repository (if you haven't already).
Code
    git init
Add your files to the staging area.
To add all changes:
Code

        git add .
To add specific files.
Code

        git add <file_name>
Commit your changes.
Replace "Initial commit" with a descriptive message.
Code

    git commit -m "Initial commit"
Add the remote repository.
Replace <YOUR_REPOSITORY_URL> with the URL of your GitHub repository.
Code

    git remote add origin <YOUR_REPOSITORY_URL>
Push your code to GitHub.
Replace main with the name of your branch if it's different.
Code

    git push -u origin main
You may be prompted to authenticate with your GitHub credentials (username and Personal Access Token or through a browser sign-in).
